transcripts:
[MUSIC PLAYING]

Look at Zucchini, one of my favorites. Of course I prefer the santoku knife. I go top to bottom. Make sure I'm always keeping my fingers back. Go right in the center, keep it nice and flat, just let the knife do the work. Of course my favorite is grilling and sauteing. So once again, same thing. All the way around. Make like a little deck of cards just go right across. Make little match sticks, throw it right on the stove top. So I got my chunks for stew, slices for grill, sticks for sauteing.
